               <msContents>
                  <summary>A copy of Kitáb-i-Aqdas. Browne notes he formerly called this work
                     "Lawḥ-i-Aqdas," a name he had heard applied to it by the Bábís in Persia, but
                     was later informed at Acre that its proper title is Kitáb-i-Aqdas, and that
                     "Lawḥ-i-Aqdas" properly denotes a separate Epistle addressed to the
                     Christians - a detail he says was independently confirmed by M.
                     Toumansky.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_30-item1">
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh, 1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_398" change="#ids-cleanup">Kitāb aqdas</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_398" change="#ids-cleanup">كتاب اقدس</title>
                   
                                          <incipit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/95">p.69</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBP. 3</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Jul., 1892): 433-499.</bibl>
                        
                        <bibl type="text-relations">Browne refers the reader to Baron Rosen, B. i, p. 495; B. ii, pp.
                           972-981 and 1007-8; and Collections Scientifiques, vi, p. 144, for further
                           description.</bibl>
                        
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
